<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-01-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                    <head>No. 333.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Anderson</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-01-07"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 7,
                            1888</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Anderson</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister, Copenhagen:</hi></p>
                    <p>Benson extradition papers mailed yesterday. Is Benson’s identity established
                        to satisfaction of Danish Government, and would prisoner be delivered to
                        United States officer now on his way from California, if send to
                        Denmark?</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bayard</hi></persName>.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>